<div class="headDiv2">
	<h2><a href="http://www.boston.com/bigpicture/2011/04/flower_power.html">Flower power</a></h2>
	<span class="blogText bigText"><div class="bpBody">The spring equinox was March 20 this year, determined by the changing sunlight and how the earth is tilted and orbits the sun.  But we don't need to look to the skies to know the seasons are turning. All we have to do is glance more earthbound to find flashes of color and bursts of life. Flowers are appearing in all kinds of places since the equinox. -- <em>Lloyd Young</em> (<a href="http://www.boston.com/bigpicture/2011/04/flower_power.html">27 photos total</a>)</div><div class="bpImageTop"><a name="photo1"></a><a href="http://www.boston.com/bigpicture/2011/04/flower_power.html"><img src="http://inapcache.boston.com/universal/site_graphics/blogs/bigpicture/flowerpower/bp1.jpg" class="bpImage" style="height:613px;width:990px" /></a><br/><div class="bpCaption">A daisy floats in a rain barrel on April 4 in Kaufbeuren, southern Germany. (Karl Josef Hildenbrand/AFP/Getty Images) <div class="cf"></div></div></div></span>

<div class="morepics"><a href="http://www.boston.com/bigpicture/2011/04/flower_power.html"><img src="http://cache.boston.com/universal/site_graphics/blogs/bigpicture/morepics1.gif" alt="more photos" onmouseout="this.src='http://cache.boston.com/universal/site_graphics/blogs/bigpicture/morepics1.gif'" onmouseover="this.src='http://cache.boston.com/universal/site_graphics/blogs/bigpicture/morepics2.gif'"></a></div>

</div>

